STRIFE · node STR · STR · STRIFE · polemos · war is the father of all · UD0 / polemos

universe of origin : the field of conflict — from the dawn of writing
seal               : Before any particular war there is strife itself — the principle of conflict. The Greeks gave it a goddess, Eris, whose golden apple 'to the fairest' set gods against one another and lit the Trojan War. And the philosopher Heraclitus made the darker claim that strife is not a flaw in the world but its engine: 'war is the father of all,' the tension that holds everything in form.
